            <h2>Chinese Family Lawyer Serving Thornhill's Established Community</h2>
            <p>Thornhill is a mature community straddling York and Peel Regions, with large Chinese-Canadian, Russian-Canadian, and Israeli-Canadian populations. The Promenade and Bayview Avenue areas are established residential zones where family law issues often involve high-value properties, RRSP portfolios, and cross-border assets. Miao He's Markham office is minutes from Thornhill, and she provides full Mandarin family law services to local clients.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2>Divorce When a Spouse Won't Cooperate</h2>
            <p>One of the most common situations Thornhill Chinese-Canadian clients face: a spouse who refuses to sign papers, delays proceedings, or denies that the marriage has broken down. In Ontario, <strong>you do not need your spouse's cooperation to get divorced</strong>. After one year of separation, Miao He can apply for divorce on your behalf — the court will grant the divorce without the other party's consent if grounds are met.</p>
            <p>She can also apply for interim orders (temporary custody, support, and property preservation) while the divorce proceeds, protecting your interests throughout.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2>Property Division in Thornhill</h2>
            <p>Thornhill homes, RRSP accounts, investment portfolios, and Chinese-held assets all form part of the Net Family Property calculation. Miao He helps clients accurately establish the value of pre-marital assets — including property brought to the marriage or received as gifts — to ensure these are properly excluded from Equalization.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2>Child Custody with Chinese Cultural Considerations</h2>
            <p>Thornhill Chinese-Canadian families often face custody disputes involving: whether children can travel to China to visit grandparents, grandparent access rights, Chinese school and language education, and Lunar New Year holiday arrangements. Miao He incorporates these cultural realities into Parenting Plans as legally binding terms — not just verbal agreements.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2>Marriage Contract &amp; Separation Agreement</h2>
            <p>Whether you are planning ahead with a Marriage Contract or settling all matters through a Separation Agreement after separation, Miao He provides full Chinese-language drafting. A Separation Agreement that resolves all property, support, and custody issues before formal divorce can save significant time and legal costs.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Question</h2>
            <p class="faq-q">My spouse refuses to cooperate with the divorce. Can I still proceed?</p>
            <p>Yes. In Ontario you can file for divorce after one year of separation — your spouse's signature is not required. Miao He can manage the entire process through the court system without your spouse's participation. Contact her at 647-930-6688.</p>
          </div>
